{"id":121793,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harlan_Ellison","text":"Harlan Jay Ellison (May 27, 1934 \u2013 June 27, 2018) was an award-winning American writer of short stories, novellas, teleplays, essays, and criticism. His most famous work is in the science fiction area, where he won many Hugo and Nebula awards.\nEllison died from cardiac arrest on June 27, 2018 at his Sherman Oaks, Los Angeles home, aged 84.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"American","offset":71},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"writer","offset":80},{"uri":"Short_stories","surface_form":"short stories","offset":90},{"uri":"Novellas","surface_form":"novellas","offset":105},{"uri":"Teleplay","surface_form":"teleplay","offset":115},{"uri":"Essays","surface_form":"essays","offset":126},{"uri":"Criticism","surface_form":"criticism","offset":138},{"uri":"Science_fiction","surface_form":"science fiction","offset":180},{"uri":"Hugo_Award","surface_form":"Hugo","offset":220},{"uri":"Nebula_Award","surface_form":"Nebula","offset":229},{"uri":"Cardiac_arrest","surface_form":"cardiac arrest","offset":262},{"uri":"Sherman_Oaks%2C_Los_Angeles","surface_form":"Sherman Oaks, Los Angeles","offset":301}]}